{"author":{"id":"cc8322a500b8739c77faac347808f6026d9ccb7880d0aaa7ad76754163cd7fdb"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1782568926,"nonce":"tPxmrDN40RQ6QCP++9Ojl7gE/4c=","kind":"plan","title":"kref Phase 1 (Core Store + Ingest Bridge) Implementation Plan"},{"type":3,"timestamp":1782568926,"nonce":"99sWXnDwPHgo1g5vkl+i3bUKbcg=","body":"# kref Phase 1 (Core Store + Ingest Bridge) Implementation Plan\n\n\u003e **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (recommended) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.\n\n**Goal:** A `kref` CLI that ingests markdown into a git-object knowledge store (built on git-bug's `entity/dag`), keeping durable docs off the working tree and out of `main`'s history, with private/shared tiers and an ingest-time secret scan.\n\n**Architecture:** Each knowledge entry is a git-bug `dag` entity — a Lamport-ordered DAG of typed operations under `refs/\u003ctier-namespace\u003e/\u003cid\u003e`, compiled to an in-memory `Snapshot`. Tiers are ref namespaces (`kref-private`, `kref-shared`); \"private never leaves\" is structural (Phase 1 has no push at all). A configured-redirect bridge ingests markdown from a gitignored `.kref/workspace/` dir into the store. `cobra` drives the CLI.\n\n**Tech Stack:** Go ≥1.25, `github.com/git-bug/git-bug/entity/dag` + `/entities/identity` + `/repository` (GPL-3.0), `github.com/spf13/cobra`, `gitleaks` binary (secret scan), `task` (Taskfile.dev).\n\n**Testing convention (MANDATORY):** **All** tests use **Ginkgo v2 + Gomega** (`github.com/onsi/ginkgo/v2`, `github.com/onsi/gomega`). No `stretchr/testify`, no bare stdlib `testing` assertions. Every package with tests gets exactly one `*_suite_test.go` bootstrap (`RegisterFailHandler(Fail); RunSpecs(...)`); specs use `Describe`/`It` and Gomega matchers. `go test ./...` runs Ginkgo suites via the bootstrap. **Exception:** the `entry` package's specs (and its suite bootstrap) use **black-box `package entry_test`**, because Ginkgo dot-imports an exported `Entry` identifier that collides with our `entry.Entry` type; reference production symbols as `entry.New`, `entry.Read`, `entry.TierShared`, etc. there. All other packages keep white-box specs.\n\n**Scope note:** Sync (`dag.Push`/`Pull`), the `kref-personal` tier, hard-prune, and lefthook wiring are **Phase 2** — out of scope here. Phase 1 is local-only and must be independently usable.\n\n**Module path (provisional):** `github.com/riotbox/kref` — change in Task 1 if the real repo path differs.\n\n---\n\n### Task 1: Project scaffold + pinned git-bug dependency\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `go.mod`, `LICENSE`, `Taskfile.yml`, `.gitignore`\n- Create: `internal/entry/entry_suite_test.go`, `internal/entry/smoke_test.go`\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Verify Go toolchain ≥1.25**\n\nRun: `go version`\nExpected: `go1.25` or newer. If absent/older, install Go 1.25+ (e.g. `dnf install -y golang` then verify; if the distro Go is older, download from go.dev). git-bug's `go.mod` requires `go 1.25.0`, so an older toolchain will fail to build.\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Initialize module and pin dependencies**\n\n```bash\ncd /workspace\ngo mod init github.com/riotbox/kref\ngo get github.com/git-bug/git-bug@latest   # records a concrete pseudo-version in go.mod\ngo get github.com/spf13/cobra@latest\ngo get github.com/onsi/ginkgo/v2@latest\ngo get github.com/onsi/gomega@latest\ngo install github.com/onsi/ginkgo/v2/ginkgo@latest   # optional CLI runner\n```\nAfter this, open `go.mod` and confirm a specific `github.com/git-bug/git-bug vX.Y.Z-...` line exists (this is our pin). Do NOT use a floating version.\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Add GPL-3.0 LICENSE**\n\n```bash\ncurl -fsSL https://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-3.0.txt -o LICENSE\nhead -1 LICENSE   # expect: \"                    GNU GENERAL PUBLIC LICENSE\"\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Add `.gitignore`**\n\n```gitignore\n/kref\n/.kref/\n/.test-output/\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Add `Taskfile.yml`** (use the `taskfile` skill to generate/lint; minimum tasks below)\n\n```yaml\nversion: '3'\n\nvars:\n  BIN: kref\n\ntasks:\n  default:\n    cmds:\n      - task --list\n    silent: true\n\n  build:\n    desc: Build the kref binary\n    cmds:\n      - go build -o ./{{.BIN}} ./cmd/kref\n\n  test:\n    desc: Run the Ginkgo suites (MODE=llm for errors-only)\n    vars:\n      FLAGS: '{{if eq .MODE \"llm\"}}-count=1{{else}}-v -count=1{{end}}'\n    cmds:\n      - go test {{.FLAGS}} ./...\n\n  lint:\n    desc: Vet and format-check\n    cmds:\n      - go vet ./...\n      - test -z \"$(gofmt -l .)\"\n\n  fmt:\n    desc: Format\n    cmds:\n      - gofmt -w .\n\n  check:\n    desc: Run fmt, lint, test\n    cmds:\n      - task: fmt\n      - task: lint\n      - task: test\n```\nRun: `bash \"$SKILL_DIR/lint.sh\"` (from the `taskfile` skill) and fix every FAIL.\n\n- [ ] **Step 6: Write the entry suite bootstrap** (`internal/entry/entry_suite_test.go`)\n\n```go\npackage entry\n\nimport (\n\t\"testing\"\n\n\t. \"github.com/onsi/ginkgo/v2\"\n\t. \"github.com/onsi/gomega\"\n)\n\nfunc TestEntry(t *testing.T) {\n\tRegisterFailHandler(Fail)\n\tRunSpecs(t, \"Entry Suite\")\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 7: Write the smoke spec** (`internal/entry/smoke_test.go`) — proves the git-bug dependency links\n\n```go\npackage entry\n\nimport (\n\t. \"github.com/onsi/ginkgo/v2\"\n\t. \"github.com/onsi/gomega\"\n\n\t\"github.com/git-bug/git-bug/entity/dag\"\n)\n\nvar _ = Describe(\"git-bug linkage\", func() {\n\tIt(\"constructs a dag.Definition\", func() {\n\t\tdef := dag.Definition{Typename: \"kref entry\", Namespace: \"kref-shared\", FormatVersion: 1}\n\t\tExpect(def.Namespace).To(Equal(\"kref-shared\"))\n\t})\n})\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 8: Run the smoke suite**\n\nRun: `go test ./internal/entry/ -run TestEntry -v`\nExpected: PASS (downloads git-bug, compiles, the spec passes).\n\n- [ ] **Step 9: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add go.mod go.sum LICENSE Taskfile.yml .gitignore internal/entry/entry_suite_test.go internal/entry/smoke_test.go\ngit commit -m \"Scaffold kref: module, pinned git-bug, GPL-3.0, Taskfile, Ginkgo\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: Entry entity — snapshot, Create op, definition, compile, read\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `internal/entry/snapshot.go`, `internal/entry/operations.go`, `internal/entry/entry.go`\n- Test: `internal/entry/entry_test.go` (suite bootstrap already exists from Task 1)\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Write the failing spec** (`internal/entry/entry_test.go`)\n\n```go\npackage entry\n\nimport (\n\t. \"github.com/onsi/ginkgo/v2\"\n\t. \"github.com/onsi/gomega\"\n\n\t\"github.com/git-bug/git-bug/entities/identity\"\n\t\"github.com/git-bug/git-bug/entity\"\n\t\"github.com/git-bug/git-bug/repository\"\n)\n\n// newTestRepo creates a throwaway repo with kref clocks loaded.\nfunc newTestRepo() repository.ClockedRepo {\n\tGinkgoHelper()\n\trepo, err := repository.InitGoGitRepo(GinkgoT().TempDir(), \"kref\")\n\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\tDeferCleanup(func() { _ = repo.Close() })\n\treturn repo\n}\n\nfunc newAuthor(repo repository.ClockedRepo) identity.Interface {\n\tGinkgoHelper()\n\tauthor, err := identity.NewIdentity(repo, \"Tester\", \"tester@example.com\")\n\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\tExpect(author.Commit(repo)).To(Succeed())\n\treturn author\n}\n\nfunc mustRead(repo repository.ClockedRepo, id entity.Id) *Entry {\n\tGinkgoHelper()\n\tgot, err := Read(repo, TierShared, id)\n\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\treturn got\n}\n\nvar _ = Describe(\"Entry create and compile\", func() {\n\tIt(\"records kind, title, and default status\", func() {\n\t\trepo := newTestRepo()\n\t\tauthor := newAuthor(repo)\n\n\t\te := New(TierShared)\n\t\te.Append(NewCreate(author, \"spec\", \"Auth design\"))\n\t\tExpect(e.Commit(repo)).To(Succeed())\n\n\t\tsnap := mustRead(repo, e.Id()).Compile()\n\t\tExpect(snap.Kind).To(Equal(\"spec\"))\n\t\tExpect(snap.Title).To(Equal(\"Auth design\"))\n\t\tExpect(snap.Status).To(Equal(\"open\"))\n\t})\n})\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Run it to verify failure**\n\nRun: `go test ./internal/entry/ -run TestEntry`\nExpected: FAIL — `New`, `NewCreate`, `Read`, `TierShared`, `Compile` undefined.\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Implement the snapshot** (`internal/entry/snapshot.go`)\n\n```go\npackage entry\n\nimport (\n\t\"time\"\n\n\t\"github.com/git-bug/git-bug/entity\"\n)\n\n// Link is a typed edge to another entry.\ntype Link struct {\n\tTo   string `json:\"to\"`\n\tType string `json:\"type\"` // relates | parent-child | supersedes | derived-from\n}\n\n// Snapshot is the compiled, read-only view of an entry.\ntype Snapshot struct {\n\tID        entity.Id\n\tKind      string\n\tTitle     string\n\tStatus    string // open | active | accepted | superseded | deleted\n\tTier      string // set by the store from the namespace it was read under\n\tBody      string\n\tLinks     []Link\n\tDeleted   bool\n\tCreatedAt time.Time\n\tUpdatedAt time.Time\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Implement the Create operation** (`internal/entry/operations.go`)\n\n```go\npackage entry\n\nimport (\n\t\"encoding/json\"\n\t\"fmt\"\n\t\"time\"\n\n\t\"github.com/git-bug/git-bug/entities/identity\"\n\t\"github.com/git-bug/git-bug/entity\"\n\t\"github.com/git-bug/git-bug/entity/dag\"\n)\n\n// Operation is a kref operation: a dag.Operation that also folds into a Snapshot.\ntype Operation interface {\n\tdag.Operation\n\tApply(*Snapshot)\n}\n\nconst (\n\t_ dag.OperationType = iota\n\tCreateOp\n\tSetStatusOp\n\tSetBodyOp\n\tAddLinkOp\n\tRemoveLinkOp\n\tTombstoneOp\n)\n\n// Create initializes an entry with a kind and title.\ntype Create struct {\n\tdag.OpBase\n\tKind  string `json:\"kind\"`\n\tTitle string `json:\"title\"`\n}\n\nfunc NewCreate(author identity.Interface, kind, title string) *Create {\n\treturn \u0026Create{\n\t\tOpBase: dag.NewOpBase(CreateOp, author, time.Now().Unix()),\n\t\tKind:   kind,\n\t\tTitle:  title,\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc (op *Create) Id() entity.Id { return dag.IdOperation(op, \u0026op.OpBase) }\n\nfunc (op *Create) Validate() error {\n\tif op.Kind == \"\" {\n\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"kind required\")\n\t}\n\tif op.Title == \"\" {\n\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"title required\")\n\t}\n\treturn op.OpBase.Validate(op, CreateOp)\n}\n\nfunc (op *Create) Apply(s *Snapshot) {\n\ts.Kind = op.Kind\n\ts.Title = op.Title\n\ts.Status = \"open\"\n\ts.CreatedAt = op.Time()\n\ts.UpdatedAt = op.Time()\n}\n\n// operationUnmarshaler decodes a stored op back into a concrete type.\nfunc operationUnmarshaler(raw json.RawMessage, _ entity.Resolvers) (dag.Operation, error) {\n\tvar t struct {\n\t\tOperationType dag.OperationType `json:\"type\"`\n\t}\n\tif err := json.Unmarshal(raw, \u0026t); err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, err\n\t}\n\tvar op dag.Operation\n\tswitch t.OperationType {\n\tcase CreateOp:\n\t\top = \u0026Create{}\n\tdefault:\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"unknown operation type %v\", t.OperationType)\n\t}\n\tif err := json.Unmarshal(raw, op); err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, err\n\t}\n\treturn op, nil\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Implement the entry wrapper, definition, and Read** (`internal/entry/entry.go`)\n\n```go\npackage entry\n\nimport (\n\t\"github.com/git-bug/git-bug/entities/identity\"\n\t\"github.com/git-bug/git-bug/entity\"\n\t\"github.com/git-bug/git-bug/entity/dag\"\n\t\"github.com/git-bug/git-bug/repository\"\n)\n\n// Tier is a visibility tier, realized as a git ref namespace.\ntype Tier string\n\nconst (\n\tTierPrivate Tier = \"private\"\n\tTierShared  Tier = \"shared\"\n)\n\nfunc (t Tier) Namespace() string { return \"kref-\" + string(t) }\n\n// AllTiers is the set of tiers present in Phase 1.\nfunc AllTiers() []Tier { return []Tier{TierPrivate, TierShared} }\n\n// Definition returns the dag.Definition for a tier (same ops, distinct namespace).\nfunc Definition(t Tier) dag.Definition {\n\treturn dag.Definition{\n\t\tTypename:             \"kref entry\",\n\t\tNamespace:            t.Namespace(),\n\t\tOperationUnmarshaler: operationUnmarshaler,\n\t\tFormatVersion:        1,\n\t}\n}\n\n// Entry wraps a dag.Entity with kref semantics.\ntype Entry struct {\n\t*dag.Entity\n}\n\nfunc wrap(e *dag.Entity) *Entry { return \u0026Entry{Entity: e} }\n\n// New creates an empty entry in the given tier.\nfunc New(t Tier) *Entry { return wrap(dag.New(Definition(t))) }\n\n// WrapForRead returns the wrapper function dag.ReadAll requires.\nfunc WrapForRead() func(*dag.Entity) *Entry { return wrap }\n\n// Compile folds the operation DAG into a Snapshot.\nfunc (e *Entry) Compile() *Snapshot {\n\tsnap := \u0026Snapshot{ID: e.Id()}\n\tfor _, op := range e.Operations() {\n\t\top.(Operation).Apply(snap)\n\t}\n\treturn snap\n}\n\nfunc resolvers(repo repository.ClockedRepo) entity.Resolvers {\n\treturn entity.Resolvers{\n\t\t\u0026identity.Identity{}: identity.NewSimpleResolver(repo),\n\t}\n}\n\n// Read loads an entry by id from a tier.\nfunc Read(repo repository.ClockedRepo, t Tier, id entity.Id) (*Entry, error) {\n\treturn dag.Read(Definition(t), wrap, repo, resolvers(repo), id)\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 6: Run the spec to verify it passes**\n\nRun: `go test ./internal/entry/ -run TestEntry -v`\nExpected: PASS. If `dag.Read`'s generic instantiation complains, confirm `*Entry` satisfies `entity.Interface` (via embedded `*dag.Entity`'s `Id()`/`Validate()`).\n\n- [ ] **Step 7: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add internal/entry/snapshot.go internal/entry/operations.go internal/entry/entry.go internal/entry/entry_test.go\ngit commit -m \"Add kref entry entity: snapshot, Create op, compile, read\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 3: Mutation operations — SetStatus, SetBody, AddLink, RemoveLink, Tombstone\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `internal/entry/operations.go` (add ops + register in unmarshaler)\n- Test: `internal/entry/operations_test.go`\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Write the failing spec** (`internal/entry/operations_test.go`, **black-box `package entry_test`**) — reuses helpers from `entry_test.go`\n\n```go\npackage entry_test\n\nimport (\n\t. \"github.com/onsi/ginkgo/v2\"\n\t. \"github.com/onsi/gomega\"\n\n\t\"github.com/riotbox/kref/internal/entry\"\n)\n\nvar _ = Describe(\"Entry mutations\", func() {\n\tIt(\"applies status, body, links, and tombstone\", func() {\n\t\trepo := newTestRepo()\n\t\tauthor := newAuthor(repo)\n\n\t\te := entry.New(entry.TierShared)\n\t\te.Append(entry.NewCreate(author, \"spec\", \"Auth design\"))\n\t\te.Append(entry.NewSetBody(author, \"# Auth\\nbody text\"))\n\t\te.Append(entry.NewSetStatus(author, \"accepted\"))\n\t\te.Append(entry.NewAddLink(author, \"kref-abc\", \"relates\"))\n\t\te.Append(entry.NewRemoveLink(author, \"kref-abc\"))\n\t\te.Append(entry.NewSetBody(author, \"updated\"))\n\t\tExpect(e.Commit(repo)).To(Succeed())\n\n\t\tsnap := mustRead(repo, e.Id()).Compile()\n\t\tExpect(snap.Status).To(Equal(\"accepted\"))\n\t\tExpect(snap.Body).To(Equal(\"updated\"))\n\t\tExpect(snap.Links).To(BeEmpty())\n\n\t\te.Append(entry.NewTombstone(author))\n\t\tExpect(e.Commit(repo)).To(Succeed())\n\t\tExpect(mustRead(repo, e.Id()).Compile().Deleted).To(BeTrue())\n\t})\n})\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Run it to verify failure**\n\nRun: `go test ./internal/entry/ -run TestEntry`\nExpected: FAIL — `NewSetBody`, `NewSetStatus`, `NewAddLink`, `NewRemoveLink`, `NewTombstone` undefined.\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Implement the operations** (append to `internal/entry/operations.go`)\n\n```go\n// SetStatus changes the entry status.\ntype SetStatus struct {\n\tdag.OpBase\n\tStatus string `json:\"status\"`\n}\n\nfunc NewSetStatus(author identity.Interface, status string) *SetStatus {\n\treturn \u0026SetStatus{OpBase: dag.NewOpBase(SetStatusOp, author, time.Now().Unix()), Status: status}\n}\nfunc (op *SetStatus) Id() entity.Id { return dag.IdOperation(op, \u0026op.OpBase) }\nfunc (op *SetStatus) Validate() error {\n\tif op.Status == \"\" {\n\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"status required\")\n\t}\n\treturn op.OpBase.Validate(op, SetStatusOp)\n}\nfunc (op *SetStatus) Apply(s *Snapshot) { s.Status = op.Status; s.UpdatedAt = op.Time() }\n\n// SetBody replaces the markdown body.\ntype SetBody struct {\n\tdag.OpBase\n\tBody string `json:\"body\"`\n}\n\nfunc NewSetBody(author identity.Interface, body string) *SetBody {\n\treturn \u0026SetBody{OpBase: dag.NewOpBase(SetBodyOp, author, time.Now().Unix()), Body: body}\n}\nfunc (op *SetBody) Id() entity.Id     { return dag.IdOperation(op, \u0026op.OpBase) }\nfunc (op *SetBody) Validate() error   { return op.OpBase.Validate(op, SetBodyOp) }\nfunc (op *SetBody) Apply(s *Snapshot) { s.Body = op.Body; s.UpdatedAt = op.Time() }\n\n// AddLink adds a typed edge.\ntype AddLink struct {\n\tdag.OpBase\n\tTo       string `json:\"to\"`\n\tLinkType string `json:\"link_type\"`\n}\n\nfunc NewAddLink(author identity.Interface, to, linkType string) *AddLink {\n\treturn \u0026AddLink{OpBase: dag.NewOpBase(AddLinkOp, author, time.Now().Unix()), To: to, LinkType: linkType}\n}\nfunc (op *AddLink) Id() entity.Id { return dag.IdOperation(op, \u0026op.OpBase) }\nfunc (op *AddLink) Validate() error {\n\tif op.To == \"\" {\n\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"link target required\")\n\t}\n\treturn op.OpBase.Validate(op, AddLinkOp)\n}\nfunc (op *AddLink) Apply(s *Snapshot) {\n\tfor _, l := range s.Links {\n\t\tif l.To == op.To \u0026\u0026 l.Type == op.LinkType {\n\t\t\treturn\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\ts.Links = append(s.Links, Link{To: op.To, Type: op.LinkType})\n\ts.UpdatedAt = op.Time()\n}\n\n// RemoveLink removes all edges to a target.\ntype RemoveLink struct {\n\tdag.OpBase\n\tTo string `json:\"to\"`\n}\n\nfunc NewRemoveLink(author identity.Interface, to string) *RemoveLink {\n\treturn \u0026RemoveLink{OpBase: dag.NewOpBase(RemoveLinkOp, author, time.Now().Unix()), To: to}\n}\nfunc (op *RemoveLink) Id() entity.Id   { return dag.IdOperation(op, \u0026op.OpBase) }\nfunc (op *RemoveLink) Validate() error { return op.OpBase.Validate(op, RemoveLinkOp) }\nfunc (op *RemoveLink) Apply(s *Snapshot) {\n\tkept := s.Links[:0]\n\tfor _, l := range s.Links {\n\t\tif l.To != op.To {\n\t\t\tkept = append(kept, l)\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\ts.Links = kept\n\ts.UpdatedAt = op.Time()\n}\n\n// Tombstone soft-deletes the entry (reversible; op-DAG retained).\ntype Tombstone struct {\n\tdag.OpBase\n}\n\nfunc NewTombstone(author identity.Interface) *Tombstone {\n\treturn \u0026Tombstone{OpBase: dag.NewOpBase(TombstoneOp, author, time.Now().Unix())}\n}\nfunc (op *Tombstone) Id() entity.Id   { return dag.IdOperation(op, \u0026op.OpBase) }\nfunc (op *Tombstone) Validate() error { return op.OpBase.Validate(op, TombstoneOp) }\nfunc (op *Tombstone) Apply(s *Snapshot) {\n\ts.Deleted = true\n\ts.Status = \"deleted\"\n\ts.UpdatedAt = op.Time()\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Register the new ops in `operationUnmarshaler`** (edit the `switch` in `operations.go`)\n\n```go\n\tswitch t.OperationType {\n\tcase CreateOp:\n\t\top = \u0026Create{}\n\tcase SetStatusOp:\n\t\top = \u0026SetStatus{}\n\tcase SetBodyOp:\n\t\top = \u0026SetBody{}\n\tcase AddLinkOp:\n\t\top = \u0026AddLink{}\n\tcase RemoveLinkOp:\n\t\top = \u0026RemoveLink{}\n\tcase TombstoneOp:\n\t\top = \u0026Tombstone{}\n\tdefault:\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"unknown operation type %v\", t.OperationType)\n\t}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Run the spec to verify it passes**\n\nRun: `go test ./internal/entry/ -run TestEntry -v`\nExpected: PASS (both Entry specs green).\n\n- [ ] **Step 6: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add internal/entry/operations.go internal/entry/operations_test.go\ngit commit -m \"Add kref entry mutation ops and tombstone\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 4: Store — open repo, identity bootstrap, Add/Get/List\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `internal/store/store.go`, `internal/store/store_suite_test.go`\n- Test: `internal/store/store_test.go`\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Verify the identity-persistence API**\n\nRead `/tmp/git-bug/entities/identity/identity.go` for the functions to (a) create from git user and (b) load a stored identity by id: confirm `NewFromGitUser(repo) (*Identity, error)`, `(*Identity).Commit(repo) error`, and `ReadLocal(repo, id) (*Identity, error)` exist with these signatures. If `NewFromGitUser` is absent, fall back to `NewIdentity(repo, name, email)` reading `repo`'s git `user.name`/`user.email` via `repo.LocalConfig()`. Record what you confirmed in a comment.\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Write the suite bootstrap** (`internal/store/store_suite_test.go`)\n\n```go\npackage store\n\nimport (\n\t\"testing\"\n\n\t. \"github.com/onsi/ginkgo/v2\"\n\t. \"github.com/onsi/gomega\"\n)\n\nfunc TestStore(t *testing.T) {\n\tRegisterFailHandler(Fail)\n\tRunSpecs(t, \"Store Suite\")\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Write the failing spec** (`internal/store/store_test.go`)\n\n```go\npackage store\n\nimport (\n\t. \"github.com/onsi/ginkgo/v2\"\n\t. \"github.com/onsi/gomega\"\n\n\t\"github.com/riotbox/kref/internal/entry\"\n)\n\nvar _ = Describe(\"Store add/get/list\", func() {\n\tIt(\"stores entries across tiers and filters by kind\", func() {\n\t\tdir := GinkgoT().TempDir()\n\t\ts, err := Init(dir, \"Tester\", \"tester@example.com\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tDeferCleanup(func() { _ = s.Close() })\n\n\t\tid, err := s.Add(entry.TierShared, \"spec\", \"Auth design\", \"# Auth\\nbody\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\n\t\tgot, err := s.Get(id)\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(got.Title).To(Equal(\"Auth design\"))\n\t\tExpect(got.Tier).To(Equal(\"shared\"))\n\n\t\t_, err = s.Add(entry.TierPrivate, \"memory\", \"secret note\", \"ssh key rotation cadence\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\n\t\tall, err := s.List(ListFilter{})\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(all).To(HaveLen(2))\n\n\t\tspecs, err := s.List(ListFilter{Kind: \"spec\"})\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(specs).To(HaveLen(1))\n\t\tExpect(specs[0].Title).To(Equal(\"Auth design\"))\n\t})\n})\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Run it to verify failure**\n\nRun: `go test ./internal/store/ -run TestStore`\nExpected: FAIL — `Init`, `Store`, `Add`, `Get`, `List`, `ListFilter` undefined.\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Implement the store** (`internal/store/store.go`